minios-session-manager (1.1.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Security improvements and code quality:
    - Add safe unmount method with retry logic and lazy unmount fallback
    - Add safe fusermount wrapper with proper error handling
    - Add safe process cleanup with timeout and SIGKILL fallback
    - Add safe directory removal with fallback to rm -rf
    - Fix context manager cleanup in mount_session_read and mount_session_write
    - Add file locking (fcntl) to prevent race conditions in session creation
    - Replace broad exception handlers with specific exception types
  * Python 3.6 compatibility:
    - Lower Python requirement from 3.7 to 3.6 for Debian 10 support
    - Replace datetime.fromisoformat() with datetime.strptime()
    - Replace capture_output=True with explicit stdout/stderr pipes
    - Replace text=True with universal_newlines=True in subprocess calls
    - Update debian/compat from 12 to 11
  * Ubuntu 18.04 compatibility:
    - Add util-linux version requirement (>= 2.31)
  * Testing infrastructure:
    - Add comprehensive pytest test suite
    - Add tests for SessionManager class (initialization, formatting, caching)
    - Add tests for union filesystem detection
    - Add tests for system version/edition detection
    - Add tests for disk space checking
    - Add tests for metadata reading/writing
    - Add tests for safe cleanup operations
    - Add pytest.ini configuration file
    - Add conftest.py with common fixtures

 -- crims0n <crims0n@minios.dev>  Mon, 19 Jan 2026 17:41:12 +0300

minios-session-manager (1.1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Core improvements:
    - Fix data copying reliability: use rsync to correctly handle special files
      and permissions
    - Fix export issues: ensure symbolic links point to correct targets in
      archives
    - Fix Native session handling: correct directory structure during
      import/export
    - Improve stability: better handling of mount points to prevent "device
      busy" errors
    - Improve cleanup: ensure temporary files are removed even if process is
      interrupted

  * Compatibility and dependencies:
    - Add support for running on tmpfs (RAM-based filesystems)
    - Add dependency on rsync package
    - Remove obsolete code for better maintainability

  * Localization:
    - Update translation files

