minios-session-manager (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Add session export and import functionality
    - Export sessions to .tar.zst archives
    - Import sessions from archives
    - Support mode change on import (native/dynfilefs/raw)
    - Automatic conversion to compatible mode
    - Skip metadata files and existing files during import
  * Add session copy and conversion functionality
    - Copy sessions with optional mode change
    - Convert existing sessions between modes
    - Support all combinations: native <> dynfilefs <> raw
  * Add full FAT32/NTFS filesystem support
    - Use fallocate instead of sparse files for raw sessions
    - Add sync after mkfs.ext4 for FAT32/NTFS compatibility
    - Remove /tmp dependency, use sessions_dir for temporary files
  * Add disk space checking for all operations
    - Check free space before creating sessions
    - Check free space before exporting (with compression overhead)
    - Check free space before importing and copying sessions
  * Fix session size handling
    - Fix size preservation during copy operations
    - Use source session size as default during conversion
    - Change default size from 4000MB to 1000MB
    - Fix GUI SpinButton range (100-100000 instead of 1000-100000)
    - Fix size_mb type conversion (string to int) in raw mode
    - Correct conversion from bytes to megabytes
  * Improve reliability
    - Fix conversion failures on FAT32 filesystems
    - Proper handling of empty sessions
    - Fix GUI crash when showing success messages
  * Add helper functions
    - Detect MiniOS version and edition
    - Bash completion for new commands
  * Update documentation
  * Update translations

 -- crims0n <crims0n@minios.dev>  Sat, 04 Oct 2025 13:25:56 +0300

